<br>
I think there are a couple reasons.  The first is general supply and demand.  The demand of items hasn’t really been affected by the new bazaar but the supply of available items for sale has shot up (the supply of those items has not changed but the availability of the items to the buying public has increased).  With the new bazaar, people can keep their character logged on while they go afk and be able to sell items where beforehand they would just log off.  Alternatively, people can use alts to store their items and always be open for business.  A separate reason (and this may be temporary) is that I believe as people went through the bazaar and found items they just had to have, they started trying to sell their existing items to enable them to purchase the new items.  When people are in a hurry to raise platinum, they will be willing to lower the price.  There is a lot of competition among sellers now, making this more of a buyer’s market.<br>
<br>
For those of us that like to adventure, this new bazaar may have been a true blessing.  I was in the bazaar for about 10 minutes last night and can see how addictive that can be.  All these items right in front of your nose that you can purchase at the drop of a dime (or several thousand pp).  There were approximately 150 people in the Bazaar when I was there last night.  What this means is that the hunting grounds may get a little less crowded as folks spend more and more time in the bazaar buying and selling wares.  This may just be a temporary phenomenon with people getting used to the new bazaar but I can see this new Bazaar creating a new breed of characters: bazaar addicts that spend all of their time in the bazaar and don’t adventure.  There will always be people that enjoy wheeling and dealing more than adventuring but this new Bazaar has increased the efficiency by which they can wheel and deal.  <br>
<br>
I may be the only one who feels this way but it looks to me as if this patch is going to have some real long-term effects on the economy of our server, in particular lower prices.<br>
<br>
Sadistik Tendonslicer<br>
Level 45 Rogue<br>
League of Honour<br>
