<br>
The lowering of prices is a sign of inflation. Those of you who have studied economics will agree. Those who haven't let me explain.<br>
<br>
By lowering the cost of items you actually raise the value of plat. It's getting to the point where a couple days of plat farming &gt; getting lucky with finding a really nice item to sell.<br>
<br>
Let's put it in the aspect of stock. You buy stock for $50 a share and buy 100 shares. You just spent $5000 on stock. Over the course of, let's say 6 months, commodities drop in price and now if you want to sell your stock, you have to take $40 a share. Sure, that's great for the guy with only $4000 in his pocket but you're out $1000. Furthermore, if you want to invest in a higher price stock, which of course your intent would be appreciation, you can look forward to your stock's actual value becoming less and less. May as well just hide your $$ in a mattress.<br>
<br>
Here's another example. Who on Karana's green plains is going to pay several K for a suit of fine steel armor now when you can spend the same money on planar armor and velious quest armor components? See, you've just made it doubly impossible for the average smith, or the average tailor for that matter. How about people selling jewelry for ungodly low prices? How are prospective jewelers supposed to make a living? How can you say this is helpful to people practicing trade skills?<br>
<br>
You who love this low plat value on commodities are ruining our server's economy. I hope you're satisfied with what you've done and continue to do. More phat loots for the people who don't want to try as hard. Grats.<br>
<br>
Well it's broken now anyway, may as well screw it up more.<br>
<br>
Long live the value of plat!  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uheagan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Heagan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>One Feisty Dwarf!</span><br>  Posts: 567<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/26/02 6:36:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2436.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The New Bazaar--Deflation and Addiction</span><hr size=1> Tomorrow the value of everything you wear will go down 2% because someone sold 8 pieces of corroded armor for 1k.<br>
