<br>
There are so many of the same item for sale and not enough people to buy them all.  Therefore, like the real world, the merchants must fight a price war to see who will sell their item.  The one willing to give the best price will make the sale and the others will be stuck waiting.  Last night alone, I saw about Five to six players in the bazaar at the same time All selling a Crystal covered shroud.  There are only so many casters out there that can benefit from getting one of these things.  This was not the only item in multiples. <br>
<br>
Yes my friends if the Supply far outways the Demand, prices will be falling.   We all can learn something else new about real life from EQ now. <br>
<br>
If you like haggling, you can still give tells to merchants (true some people just go AFK, but then they wouldn't be online otherwise so you still couldn't deal with them anyway) If they are flexible, they will come down in price.  But, if the prices are really falling so far down as everyone is complaining, WHY would you need to haggle??  Do you Haggle and try to pay the merchant MORE then he is asking??  I don't see the haggle problem.  Trades as before are still available as well if you wish to pay in other items instead of PP.  Again just give them a tell and make your offer. <p>Perimen Chath`Elghinn <BR>
